<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="twist-v">twist <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /twɪst/    美 /twɪst/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-vt-vi">1.★ <strong>vt &amp; vi (使) 弯曲；(使) 扭曲：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Twist the wire to form a circle. 
把金属丝弯成一个环。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His face twisted with pain. 
他痛苦得脸都变形了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-vt-vi">2.★ <strong>vt &amp; vi 转动 (身体等)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The visitor twisted his neck to look at the photograph on the wall behind him. 
参观者扭过头看他身后墙上的照片。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He twisted the cap off the bottle. 
他旋开了瓶盖。</p></div>

<h4 id="3-vt">3.★ <strong>vt 扭伤：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Having <strong>twisted her ankle</strong>, our tour guide had to be taken to the hospital. 
我们的导游扭伤了脚踝，不得不被送到医院。</p><footer>译林⑧ – 3</footer></div>

<h4 id="4-vi">4.★ <strong>vi 盘绕；盘旋；蜿蜒：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A snake was <strong>twisting around</strong> his arm. 
一条蛇盘绕在他的手臂上。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The river <strong>twists and turns</strong> through the green fields.
河流蜿蜒穿过绿色的田野。</p></div>

<h4 id="5vt">5.<strong>vt 歪曲；曲解：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The papers twisted everything I said. 
报纸把我说的一切都歪曲了。</p></div></div>